\int_0^1 x \sinh (x) \ \mathrm{dx}
\int f(x) g'(x)dx = f(x)g(x)-\int f'(x)g(x)dx
f(x)g(x)
\sinh(x)
\cosh(x)
\int_0^1 x\sinh(x)dx = (x\cosh(x)|_0^1 - \int_0^1 \cosh(x)dx
=\cosh(1)-[\sinh(1)-\sinh(0)] = \cosh(1) -\sinh(1) + \sinh(0)
=\cosh(1) - \sinh(1)
\int_0^1 xf(x)\,\mathrm dx = \int_0^1 f(x) \int_0^x 1 \,\mathrm dy\,\mathrm dx.
\int_0^1 1 \int_y^1 f(x) \,\mathrm dx \,\mathrm dy.
f(x) = \sinh(x)
\int_0^1 x\sinh(x)\,\mathrm dx = \int_0^1 \int_y^1 \sinh(x)\,\mathrm dx\,\mathrm dy = \int_0^1 \cosh(1) - \cosh(y)\,\mathrm dy = \cosh(1) - \sinh(1).
2\sinh(x)=e^x-e^{-x}
\int e^x(f(x)+f'(x))dx=e^xf(x)
2\int_0^1 x \sinh (x)dx=\int_0^1 xe^xdx-\int_0^1 xe^{-x}dx
=\int_0^1 e^x(x+1)dx-\int_0^1 e^{-x}(-x+1)d(-x)-\int_0^1 e^{x}dx+\int_0^1 e^{-x}d(-x)
=xe^x|_0^1-(-xe^{-x})|_0^1-e^x|_0^1+e^{-x}|_0^1
=e+\frac{1}{e}-(e-1)+(\frac{1}{e}-1)=\frac{2}{e}
2\int_0^1 x \sinh (x)dx=\frac{2}{e}\implies \int_0^1 x \sinh (x)dx=\frac{1}{e}
\sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \left(\frac{1}{(2k+2)!}-\frac{1}{(2k+3)!}\right) = \frac{1}{e}.
